title: Employments in the Netherlands 2020
summary: This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Labor force in millions, with a total of 11 data points. The chart has 3 significant trends.
The longest trend is extremely positive which exists from 2020 to 2014.
Likewise, the next significant trend is slightly negative which exists from 2014 to 2012.
On the contrary, the next significant trend is moderately positive which exists from 2012 to 2010.
gold: This statistic shows the size of the employments in the Netherlands from 2010 to 2018 , with projections up until 2020 . In 2018 , the Netherlands had employments of around 8.78 million people .
